- private visibility mode:  can't be accessed from even derived contracts whereas 'internal' can be.

- bytes(): It converts the provided data to raw bytes. A byte is represented by hex value not binary. And bytes().length provides the length of that data in hex.
        A character would have length of 1, a word of 5 character would have a length of 5.

-payable: Using it in function allows it to receive ether. amount must be specified when calling that function. msg.value captures the amount. ether is sent to
        contract's address.